│ checking for NaN handling. According to the IEEE 754 standard, `fabs`       │
│ should preserve the sign bit of NaN values, but the current transformation  │
│ doesn't account for this. The comment later in the function mentions "Note: │
│ We require 'nnan' for this fold because fcmp ignores the signbit of NAN,    │
│ but IEEE-754 specifies the signbit of NAN values with fneg/fabs             │
│ operations." This suggests that the transformation should only be applied   │
│ when the select instruction has the `nnan` (no NaN) fast math flag. Looking │
│ at the code, the first transformation (with `fsub`) doesn't check for       │
│ `nnan`, but the second transformation (with `fneg`) does check              │
│ `!SI.hasNoNaNs()`. I need to add a similar check for the `fsub` case.       │
